### 6. Design Overhaul — Ocean Sunset Palette

#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///home/jasurbek/Desktop/ozodbek/hotel/src/app/globals.css)
Replace Midnight Luxury with **Ocean Sunset**:

| Token | Light | Dark |
|---|---|---|
| `--background` | `oklch(0.97 0.01 200)` — cool white-teal | `oklch(0.13 0.04 220)` — deep ocean |
| `--foreground` | `oklch(0.18 0.05 220)` — deep navy | `oklch(0.95 0.01 200)` — soft white |
| `--primary` | `oklch(0.6 0.22 20)` — warm coral/terracotta | same |
| `--secondary` | `oklch(0.92 0.03 195)` | `oklch(0.20 0.04 215)` |
| `--card` | `oklch(1 0 0)` | `oklch(0.16 0.04 220)` |
| `--ring` | coral to match primary | same |

The body gains a subtle teal-to-transparent radial gradient.  
Primary CTAs become vivid coral-orange, links teal.

---

### 7. Environment Variables Required

```
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=app-password
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The user must create a `.env.local` with the SMTP credentials. Gmail app passwords can be generated at Google Account → Security → App Passwords.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated / Build
```bash
cd /home/jasurbek/Desktop/ozodbek/hotel
npm run build
```
 Exit code 0 = TypeScript compiles with no errors.

### Manual Verification Steps
1. **Register as Hotel Owner** — go to `/auth/register`, select "Hotel Owner", sign up, confirm redirect to `/dashboard/company`.
2. **Create a hotel** — from company dashboard add a hotel listing; confirm it appears in `/hotels`.
3. **Book as a Customer** — log in as a different user, open a hotel, pick dates, submit the booking form.
4. **Double-booking prevention** — attempt the exact same dates again; confirm a "Hotel not available" error is shown.
5. **Email notification** — check the hotel owner's inbox for the notification email from Nodemailer.
6. **Design check** — open `/` and verify the Ocean Sunset coral/teal palette renders in both light and dark mode.
